## Template D: TLS Certificate

Use this to request a TLS certificate from the platform's Vault PKI. The certificate is automatically issued and renewed by cert-manager.

```yaml
apiVersion: cert-manager.io/v1
kind: Certificate
metadata:
  name: <YOUR-APP-NAME>-tls
  namespace: <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
spec:
  secretName: <YOUR-APP-NAME>-tls-secret
  issuerRef:
    name: vault-issuer
    kind: ClusterIssuer
  dnsNames:
    - <YOUR-HOSTNAME>
  duration: 8760h
  renewBefore: 720h
```

### Verify

```bash
oc get certificate <YOUR-APP-NAME>-tls -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
# Should show READY: True
oc get secret <YOUR-APP-NAME>-tls-secret -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
```

### Mount in Your Pod

```yaml
volumes:
  - name: tls-certs
    secret:
      secretName: <YOUR-APP-NAME>-tls-secret
volumeMounts:
  - name: tls-certs
    mountPath: /etc/tls
    readOnly: true
```

